WEBVTT

00:03.235 --> 00:05.438
♪ TIMMY IS AN AVERAGE KID ♪

00:05.505 --> 00:08.308
♪ THAT NO ONE UNDERSTANDS ♪

00:08.375 --> 00:13.179
{\an1}♪ MOM AND DAD AND VICKY
ALWAYS GIVING HIM COMMANDS ♪

00:13.246 --> 00:15.682
{\an1}♪ THE DOOM AND GLOOM
UP IN HIS ROOM ♪

00:15.749 --> 00:17.917
♪ IS BROKEN INSTANTLY ♪

00:17.984 --> 00:20.553
♪ BY HIS MAGIC LITTLE FISH
WHO GRANT HIS EVERY WISH ♪

00:20.620 --> 00:23.423
{\an1}♪ 'CAUSE IN REALITY,
THEY ARE HIS... ♪

00:23.490 --> 00:25.492
{\an1}♪ ODD PARENTS,
FAIRLY ODD PARENTS ♪

00:25.558 --> 00:28.094
{\an5}♪ WANDS AND WINGS!

00:25.558 --> 00:28.094
♪ FLOATY CROWNY THINGS! ♪

00:28.161 --> 00:30.497
{\an1}♪ ODD PARENTS,
FAIRLY ODD PARENTS ♪

00:30.563 --> 00:32.966
{\an1}♪ REALLY MOD, PEA POD,
BUFF BOD, HOT ROD ♪

00:33.032 --> 00:35.502
{\an1}♪ OBTUSE, RUBBER GOOSE,
GREEN MOOSE, GUAVA JUICE ♪

00:35.568 --> 00:39.105
{\an1}♪ GIANT SNAKE, BIRTHDAY CAKE,
LARGE FRIES, CHOCOLATE SHAKE! ♪

00:39.172 --> 00:41.708
{\an1}♪ ODD PARENTS,
FAIRLY ODD PARENTS ♪

00:41.775 --> 00:44.144
♪ IT FLIPS YOUR LID
WHEN YOU'RE THE KID WITH ♪

00:44.210 --> 00:45.412
{\an8}♪ FAIRLY ODD PARENTS! ♪

00:45.478 --> 00:51.017
{\an1}YEAH,
RIGHT!

01:00.059 --> 01:03.062
{\an8}CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
NICKELODEON

01:04.364 --> 01:06.533
CRIKEY!
THE BAD PARENT HUNTER HERE,

01:06.599 --> 01:07.734
AND THIS WEEK,

01:07.801 --> 01:10.737
I'M AFTER ANOTHER SET
OF NEGLECTFUL PARENTS.

01:10.804 --> 01:13.239
HELLO, MOTHER.
HELLO, FATHER.

01:13.306 --> 01:14.874
{\an1}CAN YOU HELP ME
WITH MY HOMEWORK?

01:14.941 --> 01:16.443
{\an5}WE DON'T HAVE TIME
TO HELP YOU WITH
YOUR HOMEWORK

01:16.509 --> 01:18.545
LIKE GOOD PARENTS
SHOULD.

01:18.611 --> 01:20.547
WE'RE WATCHING
OUR FAVORITE SHOW,

01:20.613 --> 01:22.615
"THE BAD PARENT
HUNTER."

01:22.682 --> 01:24.451
YEAH! SO HERE,

01:24.517 --> 01:25.518
GO PLAY WITH THIS
DANGEROUS ACID

01:25.585 --> 01:27.020
IN THE STREET.

01:34.527 --> 01:36.429
BLOOMIN' ONION!

01:36.496 --> 01:38.298
THERE'S THEIR BOY NOW.

01:40.400 --> 01:41.801
JACKAROO CHIPS!

01:41.868 --> 01:44.437
THESE BAD PARENTS
STINK OUT LOUD.

01:44.504 --> 01:45.905
OOH! I KNOW.

01:45.972 --> 01:48.475
{\an4}LOOK AT WHAT THEY DID
TO THAT POOR KID
WHO LOOKS LIKE TIMMY.

01:48.541 --> 01:52.178
{\an5}AND LOOK AT THAT
HORRIBLE, UGLY HOUSE
THEY LIVE IN.

01:54.581 --> 01:56.850
SAFETY FIRST.

01:56.916 --> 01:58.985
WHAT'S HE DOING
HERE?

01:59.052 --> 02:01.020
{\an1}I THOUGHT HE WAS
HUNTING BAD PARENTS.

02:01.087 --> 02:03.690
{\an1}AAH!

02:01.087 --> 02:03.690
AAH!

02:04.991 --> 02:05.925
[BOTH GASP]

02:05.992 --> 02:07.527
Both: OH, MY GOSH!

02:07.594 --> 02:09.596
WE'RE THE BAD PARENTS!

02:09.662 --> 02:11.231
{\an1}RIGHT YOU ARE,
JOEY!

02:11.297 --> 02:12.765
SEE YOU NEXT TIME ON...

02:14.467 --> 02:17.670
OH! THAT'S A DIDGERIDOO!

02:21.541 --> 02:23.476
THAT WAS FUN AND DESTRUCTIVE.

02:23.543 --> 02:24.978
IT WAS FUNSTRUCTIVE!

02:25.044 --> 02:26.312
Dad: TIMMY.

02:26.379 --> 02:28.681
{\an5}BEING HUMILIATED
IN FRONT OF
A NATIONWIDE AUDIENCE

02:28.748 --> 02:30.316
HAS TAUGHT US
A LESSON.

02:30.383 --> 02:32.218
{\an1}WE ARE GOING TO BE
BETTER PARENTS.

02:32.285 --> 02:34.721
AND BY "BETTER,"
WE MEAN BOSSIER...

02:34.787 --> 02:36.589
AND MORE
IN YOUR FACE.

02:36.656 --> 02:38.691
{\an1}YEAH!
STARTING RIGHT NOW.

02:38.758 --> 02:41.461
{\an1}UNTIE US,
AND THAT'S AN ORDER!

02:41.528 --> 02:43.296
Timmy: CRIKEY!

02:43.363 --> 02:45.465
I'LL GET YOU LOSERS.

02:45.532 --> 02:46.499
OW!

02:45.532 --> 02:46.499
OW!

02:46.566 --> 02:47.500
OW!

02:46.566 --> 02:47.500
OOH!

02:47.567 --> 02:48.668
OUCH!

02:47.567 --> 02:48.668
OOH!

02:48.735 --> 02:51.337
TAKE THAT,
YOU MORONS.

02:51.404 --> 02:54.307
{\an1}WHO AREN'T ANYTHING
LIKE MY PARENTS.

02:54.374 --> 02:57.510
{\an5}NO MORE VIDEO GAMES
UNTIL YOU TAKE OUT
THE TRASH...

02:57.577 --> 02:59.445
AND DO YOUR HOMEWORK...

02:59.512 --> 03:01.214
Both: AND BRUSH YOUR TOOTH

03:01.281 --> 03:02.916
THIS INSTANT!

03:05.251 --> 03:06.352
Both: HA HA HA!

03:06.419 --> 03:09.188
WE'RE GREAT PARENTS!

03:11.357 --> 03:14.294
AND GREAT DANCERS!

03:23.736 --> 03:25.538
{\an7}UGH! MY LIFE
WAS A LOT MORE FUN

03:25.605 --> 03:28.474
{\an7}WHEN MY PARENTS DIDN'T
TELL ME WHAT TO DO
ALL THE TIME.

03:28.541 --> 03:29.776
BUT THEY'RE YOUR PARENTS.

03:29.842 --> 03:32.545
{\an1}IT'S NOT THEIR JOB
TO MAKE YOUR LIFE FUN.

03:32.612 --> 03:34.447
YEAH. PRETTY MUCH
THE OPPOSITE...

03:34.514 --> 03:35.715
LIKE WIVES.

03:36.883 --> 03:37.817
AAH!

03:37.884 --> 03:40.086
OPPOSITE.
COSMO, THAT'S IT!

03:40.153 --> 03:43.957
{\an4}I WISH TO DO
THE EXACT OPPOSITE OF
WHAT MY PARENTS SAY.

03:45.458 --> 03:47.193
WHAT?

03:47.260 --> 03:48.328
{\an1}WELL, THIS IS
USUALLY THE TIME

03:48.394 --> 03:50.129
{\an1}WHEN YOU TELL ME THAT
THIS IS A BAD WISH.

03:50.196 --> 03:52.665
{\an5}AND THAT HE
SHOULD CONSIDER
THE CONSEQUENCES,

03:52.732 --> 03:54.300
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

03:54.367 --> 03:56.469
{\an1}BECAUSE I'M
THE OPPOSITE OF FUN?

03:56.536 --> 03:59.005
[MUMBLING]

03:59.973 --> 04:01.240
WELL, NOT THIS TIME!

04:01.307 --> 04:03.543
WISH AWAY!
SEE IF I CARE!

04:03.610 --> 04:06.012
I WISH I HAD TO DO
THE EXACT OPPOSITE

04:06.079 --> 04:08.748
{\an1}OF WHATEVER MY PARENTS
TELL ME TO DO.

04:13.319 --> 04:14.621
HELLO, MOTHER.
HELLO, FATHER.

04:14.687 --> 04:15.855
CAN I WATCH TV?

04:15.922 --> 04:17.190
YOU COULD
IF I WASN'T TRYING

04:17.255 --> 04:19.425
TO BE MORE
IN YOUR FACE.

04:19.492 --> 04:21.827
YEAH. SO YOU GO
TO YOUR ROOM RIGHT NOW!

04:22.829 --> 04:26.432
OK. I WON'T GO
TO MY ROOM RIGHT NOW.

04:26.499 --> 04:28.368
THANKS!

04:29.836 --> 04:31.971
THAT'S MY BOY...

04:32.038 --> 04:33.206
AND MY POPCORN!

04:33.272 --> 04:36.476
OH, MAN, THIS IS
GONNA BE GREAT.

04:40.346 --> 04:41.948
Mom and Dad: AHEM.

04:43.383 --> 04:45.184
YOU MARCH
RIGHT UPSTAIRS

04:45.251 --> 04:47.186
AND TAKE A BATH,
YOUNG MAN.

04:47.253 --> 04:48.821
{\an1}STAY OUT HERE
AND GET FILTHY?

04:48.888 --> 04:49.956
GREAT IDEA!

05:00.800 --> 05:02.368
HEY! I WAS HERE FIRST!

05:06.839 --> 05:08.941
WHAT A GOOD SON.

05:09.008 --> 05:12.545
OH, I'M SO PROUD
OF HIS STENCH.

05:12.612 --> 05:14.614
[BEEPING]

05:16.716 --> 05:17.650
[OINK]

05:17.717 --> 05:19.185
WHAT A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

05:19.252 --> 05:21.788
{\an1}THE SUN IS SHINING,
I STILL HAVEN'T BATHED,

05:21.854 --> 05:24.791
AND THIS OPPOSITE THING
IS AWESOME.

05:26.192 --> 05:27.593
AHH!

05:27.660 --> 05:28.695
{\an1}THERE'S NOTHING
MORE MANLY

05:28.761 --> 05:31.097
{\an1}THAN LIVING
IN NATURE'S FILTH.

05:31.164 --> 05:33.566
{\an1}WHAT A GREAT WISH,
TIMMY.

05:33.633 --> 05:34.567
WHAT?

05:34.634 --> 05:35.768
THIS IS USUALLY THE TIME

05:35.835 --> 05:38.004
{\an1}WHEN YOU TELL US
TO UNWISH THE WISH.

05:38.071 --> 05:40.206
AND THAT IF WE DON'T
IT'LL BE REALLY BAD,

05:40.273 --> 05:43.109
{\an1}BECAUSE YOU'RE SO SMART
AND I'M SO DUMB

05:43.176 --> 05:45.445
{\an1}AND BLAH,
BLAH, BLAH.

05:45.511 --> 05:47.146
[GRUNTING]

05:47.213 --> 05:48.414
NOT THIS TIME!

05:48.481 --> 05:50.216
I'M FUN WANDA,
REMEMBER?

05:50.283 --> 05:52.919
I'M LOVING THIS!

05:52.985 --> 05:54.253
WHA-HA!

05:55.488 --> 05:58.057
{\an5}WELL, I GUESS
I'D BETTER GO
CATCH THE BUS,

05:58.124 --> 05:59.726
{\an1}UNLESS YOU WANT TO TELL ME
SOMETHING LIKE,

05:59.792 --> 06:02.028
{\an1}"DON'T BE LATE,"
OR "GO TO SCHOOL,"

06:02.095 --> 06:03.596
OR "DON'T PRETEND
TO BE SICK

06:03.663 --> 06:04.931
"AND STAY HOME
PLAYING VIDEO GAMES

06:04.997 --> 06:06.799
AND EATING
CHEESY PRETZELS."

06:06.866 --> 06:07.934
NO, NO.

06:08.000 --> 06:09.068
JUST BE GOOD.

06:11.337 --> 06:12.872
UH-OH!

06:16.309 --> 06:18.344
[CACKLING]

06:20.379 --> 06:22.648
{\an1}OH, NO. HIS DAD
TOLD HIM TO BE GOOD,

06:22.715 --> 06:24.917
{\an4}AND THAT MEANS
HE'S GOING TO BE
THE OPPOSITE--

06:24.984 --> 06:27.153
EVIL, PURE EVIL.

06:27.220 --> 06:29.489
{\an1}DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS?

06:29.555 --> 06:31.457
YEAH. THIS IS
GONNA BE FUN...

06:31.524 --> 06:34.293
UNLESS YOU WANT HIM
TO UNWISH THE WISH.

06:34.360 --> 06:35.261
NO!

06:35.328 --> 06:38.598
HOW NOT FUN
WOULD THAT BE?

06:38.664 --> 06:40.299
SEE? ISN'T THIS FUN?

06:40.366 --> 06:42.335
[BELL RINGS]

06:49.475 --> 06:51.778
YAHH!

06:51.844 --> 06:54.514
{\an1}TURNER, I DON'T LIKE
THAT EVIL LOOK IN YOUR EYE.

06:54.580 --> 06:56.449
{\an1}THAT'S THE EVIL LOOK
IN MY EYE.

06:56.516 --> 06:57.850
{\an1}ONLY ONE OF US
CAN HAVE IT.

06:57.917 --> 06:59.519
WHO'S IT GONNA BE?

07:00.820 --> 07:02.555
{\an1}I THOUGHT YOU
ONLY HAD ONE TOOTH.

07:02.622 --> 07:05.291
AAH!

07:05.358 --> 07:07.260
APPARENTLY IT'S HIM.

07:07.326 --> 07:10.062
{\an1}THIS COULD ONLY BE
THE WORK OF...

07:10.129 --> 07:11.631
FAIRY BAD PARENTS!

07:11.697 --> 07:12.832
OH, WELL. TIME TO
SEEK A NEW CAREER

07:12.899 --> 07:14.867
{\an1}THAT DOESN'T CROSS PATHS
WITH THE EVIL TURNER.

07:14.934 --> 07:16.002
WOW, WANDA.

07:16.068 --> 07:16.969
I HAVE TO SAY,

07:17.036 --> 07:18.137
{\an1}YOU'RE REALLY
DOING A GOOD JOB

07:18.204 --> 07:20.173
{\an1}NOT RAINING ON
TIMMY'S EVIL PARADE.

07:20.239 --> 07:23.976
OK. SO TIMMY GETS
TO BE THE BAD BOY.

07:24.043 --> 07:26.312
WHAT'S THE WORST
THAT CAN HAPPEN?

07:26.379 --> 07:28.314
[THUNDER]

07:28.381 --> 07:30.082
[ORGAN MUSIC]

07:31.250 --> 07:32.218
Female voice:
PREPARING TO FIRE

07:32.285 --> 07:35.221
THE SUPER-DEADLY
EVIL SUPER LASER

07:35.288 --> 07:38.858
IN ONE SUPER-EVIL MINUTE
AND COUNTING.

07:40.426 --> 07:42.161
THAT'S THE WORST.

07:43.529 --> 07:44.530
IN JUST SECONDS,

07:44.597 --> 07:46.933
{\an1}MY SUPER-DEADLY
EVIL SUPER-EVIL LASER

07:46.999 --> 07:48.434
WILL FIRE INTO SPACE

07:48.501 --> 07:51.204
{\an1}AND KNOCK DOWN THIS
COMMUNICATIONS SATELLITE!

07:51.270 --> 07:53.072
OH, WAIT.
THAT'S THE WORST.

07:54.173 --> 07:56.409
CAUSING IT TO CRASH
INTO MT. DIMMSDALE

07:56.475 --> 07:59.378
{\an1}AND REACTIVATE
THE DORMANT VOLCANO.

07:59.445 --> 08:01.047
NOPE. THAT IS.

08:01.113 --> 08:02.515
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:02.582 --> 08:03.950
I'M JUST SETTING UP
THE CAMERA

08:04.016 --> 08:05.251
FOR WHEN IT HAPPENS.

08:05.318 --> 08:06.452
WHEN WHAT HAPPENS?

08:06.519 --> 08:10.223
{\an7}THEN THE LAVA WILL BURST
THE DIMMSDALE DAM.

08:10.289 --> 08:11.624
THEN THE RESULTING FLOOD

08:11.691 --> 08:15.761
WILL CAUSE A MELTDOWN OF
THE DIMMSDALE MAKE-UP FACTORY.

08:15.828 --> 08:18.364
AND ONCE PEOPLE HAVE NO MAKE-UP,

08:18.431 --> 08:20.366
ALL SOCIAL LIFE IN DIMMSDALE
WILL COLLAPSE,

08:20.433 --> 08:23.803
AND LIFE IN DIMMSDALE
WILL CEASE TO EXIST!

08:23.870 --> 08:26.305
AAH!

08:27.306 --> 08:28.374
HE'S RIGHT!

08:28.441 --> 08:30.376
{\an1}SOME PEOPLE LOOK TERRIBLE
WITHOUT MAKE-UP.

08:30.443 --> 08:34.280
{\an4}NOBODY'S EVER SEEN COSMO
WITHOUT HIS PANCAKE BASE
AND BLUSH.

08:34.347 --> 08:36.182
OH, IT'S HORRIBLE!

08:36.249 --> 08:37.515
WHOA!

08:37.582 --> 08:39.318
HEY! THAT'S
OUR LITTLE SECRET.

08:39.385 --> 08:40.486
BUT USE THAT TERROR.

08:40.553 --> 08:42.154
YEAH, BABY,
WORK THE TERROR.

08:42.221 --> 08:43.188
[SCREAMING]

08:43.256 --> 08:45.157
WORK IT, BABY!
YEAH, THAT'S IT!

08:45.224 --> 08:47.360
OH, YEAH!
OH! I LOVE IT!

08:47.426 --> 08:48.828
GOOD EVENING, SIR.

08:48.895 --> 08:51.631
{\an4}I'M DENZEL CROCKER
OF THE DOOR-TO-DOOR
HAM COMPANY

08:51.697 --> 08:53.032
OF CANTON, OHIO.

08:53.099 --> 08:54.667
[GROWLS]

08:54.734 --> 08:56.636
AAH!

08:56.702 --> 08:59.105
AAH!

09:01.173 --> 09:02.341
OH, WELL.

09:02.408 --> 09:04.310
{\an1}TIME FOR ME TO PURSUE
A CAREER AS A TOUR GUIDE.

09:04.377 --> 09:07.046
Female voice: SUPER-EVIL LASER
READY TO FIRE.

09:07.113 --> 09:09.315
[TIMMY CACKLING]

09:09.382 --> 09:10.583
Wanda: COSMO!

09:10.650 --> 09:11.984
WE HAVE TO STOP
TIMMY!

09:12.051 --> 09:13.286
WELL, FINALLY!

09:13.352 --> 09:14.353
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

09:14.420 --> 09:16.222
{\an1}HOW COULD YOU
LET IT GO THIS FAR?

09:16.289 --> 09:17.490
Mom: SEE?

09:18.724 --> 09:20.393
{\an1}I TOLD YOU HE HAD
TURNED THE LIVING ROOM

09:20.459 --> 09:22.161
INTO AN EVIL LAIR.

09:22.228 --> 09:24.096
{\an5}I DON'T REMEMBER
TELLING HIM
TO DO THAT.

09:24.163 --> 09:25.765
TIMMY,
GO TO YOUR ROOM!

09:30.770 --> 09:32.238
WHAT ROOM?

09:35.141 --> 09:36.409
NOW, IF YOU'LL
EXCUSE ME,

09:36.475 --> 09:39.912
IT'S TIME TO WATCH
MY EVIL PLAN UNFOLD.

09:39.979 --> 09:42.915
OK. THAT IS IT,
EVIL YOUNG MAN!

09:42.982 --> 09:46.719
{\an4}DID I MENTION THAT MY LASER
COULD ALSO BLOW UP
DINKLEBERG'S HOUSE?

09:46.786 --> 09:48.421
EH...
HANG ON A SECOND.

09:48.487 --> 09:50.957
{\an5}I THINK OUR EVIL BOY
MIGHT BE ON
TO SOMETHING HERE.

09:56.662 --> 09:58.331
{\an1}Crocker: WELCOME
TO THE DIMMSDALE DAM.

09:58.397 --> 10:00.032
BUILT IN 1948,

10:00.099 --> 10:03.002
{\an1}IT IS IMPERVIOUS TO
ANY NATURAL DISASTER...

10:03.069 --> 10:04.570
{\an1}EXCEPT FOR
A HUGE LAVA FLOW,

10:04.637 --> 10:06.539
{\an1}BUT WHAT ARE
THE ODDS OF THAT?

10:06.605 --> 10:07.606
AAH!

10:09.742 --> 10:10.743
YAH!

10:13.012 --> 10:14.447
YAH!

10:14.513 --> 10:17.283
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

10:17.350 --> 10:18.317
Mom: OHH!

10:18.384 --> 10:19.585
THE MAKE-UP
FACTORY.

10:19.652 --> 10:21.587
{\an5}THAT'S THE PLACE
THAT MAKES YOUR DAD
LOOK PRETTY.

10:21.654 --> 10:23.956
WE HAVE TO
DO SOMETHING!

10:24.023 --> 10:26.192
{\an5}NOW, HONEY,
IF TIMMY WANTS
TO BE EVIL

10:26.258 --> 10:27.660
AND DESTROY
THE DINKLEBERGS' HOUSE,

10:27.727 --> 10:30.296
THEN I SAY GO AHEAD.

10:30.363 --> 10:31.330
HI, TURNER!

10:31.397 --> 10:33.399
BYE, DINKLEBERG!

10:33.466 --> 10:36.736
{\an5}TIMMY, I WANT YOU
TO BE AS EVIL
AS POSSIBLE.

10:40.072 --> 10:41.640
[SCREAMING]

10:41.707 --> 10:44.944
{\an5}OH, NO!
MY MOTHER IS NOTHING
WITHOUT HER MAKE-UP!

10:45.011 --> 10:48.314
{\an5}OH, NO! YOUR FATHER
IS NOTHING WITHOUT
HIS MAKE-UP!

10:48.381 --> 10:49.582
{\an7}AND I'M NOTHING
WITHOUT MY EYELINER

10:49.648 --> 10:50.850
{\an8}AND TOOTH GLOSS.

10:50.916 --> 10:53.052
{\an8}I WISH THAT WAVE WAS GONE!

10:56.489 --> 10:57.890
YAH!

10:57.957 --> 10:58.958
OOF!

10:59.959 --> 11:01.260
HA! I'M ALIVE,

11:01.327 --> 11:03.229
AND I LOOK FANTASTIC.

11:03.295 --> 11:05.464
{\an4}YAY!
THE DEADLY WAVE
IS GONE,

11:05.531 --> 11:07.466
{\an1}AND TIMMY IS
BACK TO NORMAL.

11:07.533 --> 11:09.535
AND WHEN DID WE
GET THOSE CATS?

11:09.602 --> 11:10.936
SORRY, MOM AND DAD.

11:11.003 --> 11:14.006
I WAS JUST GOING THROUGH
AN EVIL PHASE,

11:14.073 --> 11:15.107
WHICH IS OVER FOR GOOD

11:15.174 --> 11:18.177
BECAUSE YOU'RE BOTH
SUCH GOOD PARENTS.

11:19.245 --> 11:20.746
AWW.

11:20.813 --> 11:22.681
{\an1}LET'S GO HAVE
SOME ICE CREAM.

11:22.748 --> 11:24.083
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

11:24.150 --> 11:25.618
Dad: I'LL BE RIGHT THERE,

11:25.684 --> 11:28.054
AS SOON AS I SAY GOOD-BYE
TO DINKLEBERG.

11:28.120 --> 11:29.388
{\an1}ALL OF US!

11:29.455 --> 11:31.323
MMM.
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

11:31.390 --> 11:34.093
{\an1}MAN, THAT WAS
TOO CLOSE!

11:34.160 --> 11:36.062
AND I HOPE YOU
LEARNED YOUR LESSON.

11:36.128 --> 11:37.263
FROM NOW ON,

11:37.329 --> 11:38.764
{\an5}DO A BETTER JOB
OF KEEPING TRACK
OF TIMMY,

11:38.831 --> 11:39.765
LIKE ME!

11:39.832 --> 11:41.700
BECAUSE YOU'RE
SO RESPONSIBLE,

11:41.767 --> 11:43.836
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH,

11:43.903 --> 11:45.905
AND I'M SUCH A NAG,

11:45.971 --> 11:47.540
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

11:47.606 --> 11:49.442
STOP MOCKING ME!

11:55.681 --> 11:58.017
{\an1}YOU SHOULD PUT
SOME MAKE-UP ON, MAN.

11:58.084 --> 11:59.552
CRIKEY!

12:15.734 --> 12:18.704
Man on radio:
GOOD MORNING, FANS OF FUN.

12:18.771 --> 12:21.207
HEY, BE SURE TO GET
TO ADRENALAND EARLY

12:21.273 --> 12:23.309
{\an1}TO GET THAT PERFECT
PARKING SPACE.

12:23.375 --> 12:25.344
[SNORING]

12:27.446 --> 12:29.014
HEY, DINKLEBERG,

12:29.081 --> 12:30.883
THERE'S A BUG
ON YOUR NOSE.

12:31.884 --> 12:33.786
[TIRES SCREECH]

12:46.699 --> 12:48.033
AARGH!

12:52.671 --> 12:53.639
DID SOMEBODY KNOCK?

12:53.706 --> 12:54.707
[BELCH]

12:59.211 --> 13:02.214
WOW!
THIS PARK IS GREAT.

13:02.281 --> 13:03.349
{\an1}THAT HURT.

13:03.415 --> 13:05.084
All: YAY!

13:05.151 --> 13:07.720
{\an5}Dad: I TOLD YOU
LEAVING EARLY
WAS A GREAT IDEA.

13:07.786 --> 13:09.388
THIS IS THE BEST
PARKING SPOT

13:09.455 --> 13:11.123
WE'VE EVER GOTTEN
AT ADRENALAND.

13:13.993 --> 13:16.128
AND THERE'S THE HEART STOPPER,

13:16.195 --> 13:21.867
{\an4}THE TOUGHEST, BESTEST,
AND MOST LAWSUIT-PRONE
ROLLER COASTER IN THE WORLD!

13:23.536 --> 13:24.970
[SIRENS]

13:25.037 --> 13:26.839
OK, BUT REMEMBER,

13:26.906 --> 13:29.375
{\an1}WE MEET HERE
AT EXACTLY 5:00 OR...

13:30.609 --> 13:32.578
{\an1}WOW. HE NEVER
MOVES THAT FAST

13:32.645 --> 13:34.480
{\an1}WHEN IT'S TIME
FOR CHORES.

13:34.547 --> 13:36.282
{\an4}Man: UH, MA'AM,
DID YOU LOSE
YOUR CHILD?

13:36.348 --> 13:40.019
{\an1}THEY CAN HELP YOU
OVER HERE.

13:40.085 --> 13:42.288
BUT WE DIDN'T
LOSE OUR CHILD.

13:42.354 --> 13:44.657
{\an1}THAT'S THE PASSWORD.
WELCOME!

13:48.060 --> 13:51.096
Both: AAH!

13:54.533 --> 13:59.104
Woman: WELCOME TO ADULT LAND.

13:59.171 --> 14:00.839
OH, MY GOSH.

14:00.906 --> 14:03.209
IT'S A KIDLESS ADULT PARADISE.

14:03.275 --> 14:04.710
HEY,
THAT'S GREAT!

14:04.777 --> 14:07.680
WE CAN USE THAT
AS OUR SLOGAN.

14:08.981 --> 14:10.249
Both: CHEERS!

14:13.252 --> 14:14.787
HEART CONDITION?
GO AHEAD.

14:14.853 --> 14:16.655
{\an5}HIGH BLOOD
PRESSURE?
RIGHT THIS WAY.

14:16.722 --> 14:18.090
THIS IS GONNA BE
GREAT.

14:18.157 --> 14:20.793
I CAN'T WAIT TO
RIDE THIS RIDE.

14:20.859 --> 14:22.228
YOU CAN'T
RIDE THIS RIDE.

14:22.294 --> 14:23.729
WHAT?

14:23.796 --> 14:25.631
YOU'RE
WAY TOO SMALL.

14:25.698 --> 14:27.132
BUT DON'T WORRY,
KIDS.

14:27.199 --> 14:30.135
{\an5}THERE'S PLENTY OF
EXCITING RIDES
FOR KIDS YOUR SIZE,

14:30.202 --> 14:32.671
LIKE THE SNAIL-GO-ROUND...

14:32.738 --> 14:34.006
WHEE?

14:34.073 --> 14:36.208
OR IT'S A DULL WORLD.

14:36.275 --> 14:38.143
{\an1}YAY!

14:38.210 --> 14:39.445
OHH.

14:39.511 --> 14:41.780
OH, MAN! THIS REEKS!

14:45.618 --> 14:47.019
[CHEWING]

14:47.086 --> 14:47.987
[GULP]

14:48.053 --> 14:49.555
THIS SO DOES NOT REEK!

14:49.622 --> 14:51.523
THAT'S A GREAT
SLOGAN, TOO.

14:54.693 --> 14:55.794
"LOSING OUR SON"

14:55.861 --> 14:58.831
{\an1}WAS THE BEST THING
THAT EVER HAPPENED TO US.

14:58.897 --> 15:00.132
WE HAVE A SON?

15:00.199 --> 15:02.201
[GRUNTING]

15:04.069 --> 15:05.504
AAH!

15:05.571 --> 15:06.572
GIVE IT UP, TIMMY.

15:06.639 --> 15:07.840
BY MY CALCULATIONS,

15:07.906 --> 15:09.908
{\an4}NONE OF US WILL BE
TALL ENOUGH TO
RIDE THAT RIDE

15:09.975 --> 15:11.377
UNTIL WE'RE 16 YEARS OLD.

15:11.443 --> 15:15.748
{\an1}GOOD THING WE BROUGHT
OUR EMERGENCY TALL KID KIT.

15:20.219 --> 15:22.955
COOL!
WE'RE ADULT-SIZED.

15:23.022 --> 15:24.390
NOW WHAT?

15:24.456 --> 15:26.992
NOW YOU COME WITH ME

15:27.059 --> 15:28.894
{\an1}BECAUSE YOU JUST
LOST YOUR SON.

15:28.961 --> 15:30.062
WE--I--

15:30.129 --> 15:31.597
I DIDN'T LOSE MY SON.

15:31.664 --> 15:33.766
{\an1}AND THAT'S
THE PASSWORD.

15:33.832 --> 15:34.767
AAH!

15:34.833 --> 15:37.236
CHESTER? A.J.? OH, GREAT.

15:37.303 --> 15:39.004
{\an5}NOW I'M TOO SHORT
AND THERE'S
NOBODY ELSE AROUND

15:39.071 --> 15:40.673
TO BE MISERABLE WITH ME!

15:40.739 --> 15:42.141
NOT TRUE.

15:42.207 --> 15:44.410
LOOK. I'M EVERYBODY'S
FAVORITE WASTE-FILTERING ORGAN,

15:44.476 --> 15:45.844
KENNY KIDNEY!

15:45.911 --> 15:48.914
{\an1}AND I'M, UH,
PENNY PANCREAS.

15:48.981 --> 15:50.049
AND I NEED TO
GET TALL ENOUGH

15:50.115 --> 15:51.684
TO GET ON THAT RIDE!

15:51.750 --> 15:54.553
AND I AM NOT
WAITING UNTIL PUBERTY!

15:54.620 --> 15:57.756
{\an1}I WISH I HAD THE BODY
OF A 16-YEAR-OLD!

15:57.823 --> 15:59.458
{\an1}ONE GROWTH SPURT
COMING UP.

16:09.401 --> 16:11.770
COOL! I'VE GOT THE BRAIN
OF A 10-YEAR-OLD

16:11.837 --> 16:13.172
IN A 16-YEAR-OLD
BODY.

16:13.238 --> 16:14.473
YOU KNOW WHAT
THAT MEANS?

16:14.540 --> 16:15.674
YOU'RE A SUPERMODEL?

16:15.741 --> 16:18.977
YEP, AND IT'S TIME
TO RIDE SOME RIDES.

16:19.044 --> 16:21.980
{\an8}AND COUNT SOME OF
THOSE NEW HAIRS
ON YOUR CHIN.

16:22.047 --> 16:23.115
All: YAY!

16:23.182 --> 16:25.684
{\an1}IT'S OUR FAVORITE
WASTE-FILTERING ORGAN,

16:25.751 --> 16:27.586
KENNY KIDNEY!

16:27.653 --> 16:28.620
[CHEERING]

16:28.687 --> 16:30.389
WHAT ABOUT ME?

16:30.456 --> 16:31.857
I'M A PANCREAS.

16:31.924 --> 16:33.192
YEAH, RIGHT!

16:33.258 --> 16:35.060
YOU'RE NOT EVEN
A VITAL ORGAN.

16:35.127 --> 16:36.128
MY DAD HAD
YOU REMOVED

16:36.195 --> 16:37.930
AT AGE 32.

16:37.996 --> 16:40.132
YOU CAN BE REMOVED?

16:47.740 --> 16:48.974
NOW, WHAT TIME

16:49.041 --> 16:51.310
{\an5}WERE WE SUPPOSED
TO MEET TIMMY,
CHESTER, AND A.J.?

16:51.377 --> 16:53.512
{\an1}5:00.

16:53.579 --> 16:55.681
{\an1}OOH! YOU'VE DROPPED
YOUR MUSTACHE.

16:55.748 --> 16:57.015
{\an1}I GOT IT!

16:59.952 --> 17:00.886
TALL BOY COMING THROUGH.

17:00.953 --> 17:02.454
10 NEW HAIRS.
HERE I COME,

17:02.521 --> 17:04.223
{\an1}OBVIOUSLY MEETING
ALL HEIGHT REQUIREMENTS.

17:04.289 --> 17:06.058
GREAT! I NEED
A SINGLE RIDER.

17:06.125 --> 17:08.527
{\an1}OH, MAN!
THIS IS AWESOME!

17:08.594 --> 17:11.663
{\an1}HEY, CUTIE,
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

17:11.730 --> 17:12.664
GAH!

17:12.731 --> 17:15.067
{\an1}GAH? WHAT KIND OF
NAME IS GAH?

17:15.134 --> 17:17.536
GAH? OH, IT'S, UH...

17:17.603 --> 17:19.538
NORWEGIAN?

17:19.605 --> 17:21.339
{\an1}HMM.
NORWEGIAN, HUNKY...

17:21.406 --> 17:22.473
[GASP]

17:22.540 --> 17:24.242
{\an1}ARE YOU A NORWEGIAN
SUPERMODEL?

17:24.309 --> 17:26.211
UH...I GUESS?

17:26.278 --> 17:27.246
AAH!

17:27.311 --> 17:28.981
THOSE ARE THE TOP
TWO REQUIREMENTS

17:29.048 --> 17:30.549
FOR MY DREAM MAN!

17:30.616 --> 17:31.617
{\an1}OH, GAH!

17:31.683 --> 17:33.552
{\an1}I'M NEVER LETTING YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT.

17:33.619 --> 17:35.554
{\an1}HOW DO YOU SAY
"I LOVE YOU" IN NORWEGIAN?

17:35.621 --> 17:36.555
HELP?

17:36.622 --> 17:38.791
{\an1}OH!
I LOVE YOUR ACCENT.

17:38.857 --> 17:41.160
IT'S NORWEGILICIOUS.

17:42.628 --> 17:44.797
{\an1}HANG ON TO ME TIGHT,
GAH.

17:44.863 --> 17:47.499
{\an5}ARE YOU NUTS?
WHY WOULD I
HANG ON TO YOU?

17:49.868 --> 17:51.904
AAH! MY SAFETY BELT!

17:51.970 --> 17:54.306
[SCREAMING]

18:06.084 --> 18:07.820
Man: CLEAR!

18:07.886 --> 18:08.821
{\an1}SO, GAH,

18:08.887 --> 18:11.089
{\an1}DO YOU, UH,
WANT TO RIDE IT AGAIN?

18:11.156 --> 18:12.090
HELP!

18:12.157 --> 18:13.525
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

18:13.592 --> 18:14.760
AAH!

18:14.827 --> 18:15.961
YAH!

18:16.028 --> 18:18.931
{\an1}GAH, I WILL FOLLOW YOU
TO THE END OF THE EARTH,

18:18.997 --> 18:22.034
UNTIL SOMEONE RICHER
OR BETTER-LOOKING SHOWS UP.

18:23.569 --> 18:25.170
[VICKY LAUGHING]

18:28.574 --> 18:30.375
{\an1}BUCKTEETH AND PINK HAT
ON A KID?

18:30.442 --> 18:31.710
EWW.

18:31.777 --> 18:32.978
BUCKTEETH AND PINK HAT

18:33.045 --> 18:35.047
{\an1}ON A NORWEGIAN MALE
SUPERMODEL?

18:35.113 --> 18:36.381
YAY!

18:36.448 --> 18:37.449
[LAUGHTER AND CHEERING]

18:37.516 --> 18:38.851
COSMO, WANDA, HELP ME!

18:38.917 --> 18:40.018
{\an1}VICKY WON'T
LEAVE ME ALONE.

18:40.085 --> 18:42.120
I CAN'T HAVE
ANY MORE FUN.

18:42.187 --> 18:44.356
{\an1}I WISH
I WASN'T 16 ANYMORE!

18:44.423 --> 18:48.327
{\an5}AND I WISH I WASN'T
STUCK IN THIS STUPID
KIDNEY SUIT,

18:48.393 --> 18:51.129
{\an5}BUT WE CAN'T ALL BE
NORWEGIAN MALE
SUPERMODELS,

18:51.196 --> 18:52.297
NOW, CAN WE?

18:52.364 --> 18:53.832
AAH!

18:57.536 --> 19:01.240
{\an5}LOOK! GAH,
THE NORWEGIAN
SUPERMODEL!

19:01.306 --> 19:02.407
YAY!

19:02.474 --> 19:05.677
{\an5}OH, GAH!
THIS IS GONNA BE
SO FUN.

19:05.744 --> 19:07.179
YEAH, FOR ME.

19:07.246 --> 19:08.480
IF I CAN'T
SHAKE HER LOOSE,

19:08.547 --> 19:10.616
MAYBE I CAN
SMASH HER LOOSE.

19:10.682 --> 19:12.017
AH, MR. GAH,

19:12.084 --> 19:13.986
{\an5}WOULD YOU MIND
IF I TOOK YOUR
PICTURE AND THEN...

19:14.052 --> 19:15.354
SOLD IT
ON THE INTERNET?

19:18.023 --> 19:18.957
NO, THANKS.

19:19.024 --> 19:20.726
I HAVE MY OWN.

19:20.792 --> 19:22.628
HA HA HA!

19:24.062 --> 19:25.597
GAH, WILL YOU
SIGN THIS CALENDAR

19:25.664 --> 19:27.266
I BOUGHT OFF
THE INTERNET?

19:27.332 --> 19:28.534
I HAVE A CALENDAR?

19:28.600 --> 19:30.035
Girl: AAH!

19:30.102 --> 19:31.537
STOP FLIRTING
WITH HIM!

19:31.603 --> 19:33.572
HE'S MINE!

19:44.983 --> 19:47.920
DID YOU HEAR?
GAH'S IN THE PARK.

19:47.986 --> 19:49.087
NO WAY. WOW.

19:49.154 --> 19:51.089
UH, YOU REALLY SEEM
TO HAVE A KNOT HERE.

19:51.156 --> 19:52.958
{\an1}SURE YOU DON'T WANT
TO TAKE OFF YOUR COAT?

19:53.025 --> 19:55.193
{\an1}UH...

19:57.362 --> 19:58.964
All: CHILDREN?

20:00.632 --> 20:02.067
{\an1}WE'VE GOT A RUNNER
IN QUADRANT 7.

20:02.134 --> 20:04.269
{\an4}THE OLD FAKE MUSTACHE,
SIT ON EACH OTHER'S
SHOULDERS,

20:04.336 --> 20:05.737
{\an1}HIDE IN A TRENCH COAT
TRICK.

20:05.804 --> 20:08.240
{\an1}OK. TIME TO GO BACK
TO THE OTHER PARK

20:08.307 --> 20:10.108
AND "FIND YOUR KIDS."

20:10.175 --> 20:11.944
NO!
NO, PLEASE!

20:12.010 --> 20:14.580
DID WE MENTION
GAH IS IN THE PARK?

20:14.646 --> 20:16.081
[CHEERING]

20:16.148 --> 20:18.684
GAH?
HE'S NORWEGILICIOUS.

20:18.750 --> 20:21.720
{\an1}I'VE GONE GAGA
OVER GAH!

20:23.188 --> 20:24.990
GAH!

20:25.057 --> 20:29.728
PLAYING HARD TO GET
ONLY MAKES ME WANT YOU MORE!

20:32.030 --> 20:33.899
OH, MAN! IT'S ALMOST 5:00.

20:33.966 --> 20:35.968
I GOT TO FIND COSMO AND WANDA.

20:39.338 --> 20:40.906
COSMO! WANDA!

20:40.973 --> 20:42.341
OH!
I DON'T BELIEVE IT!

20:42.407 --> 20:44.009
IT'S GAH!

20:44.076 --> 20:45.777
WILL YOU SIGN
MY KIDNEY STONES?

20:47.045 --> 20:48.814
FINALLY!
YOU GOT TO HELP ME.

20:48.880 --> 20:51.316
VICKY'S FALLEN FOR
THE 16-YEAR-OLD ME,

20:51.383 --> 20:55.187
{\an4}AND EVERYBODY THINKS
I'M A HUNKY NORWEGIAN
MALE SUPERMODEL.

20:55.253 --> 20:56.254
HELP!

20:56.321 --> 20:58.190
{\an1}WELL, WE CAN'T
EXACTLY CHANGE YOU BACK

20:58.256 --> 21:00.692
{\an1}RIGHT HERE WHERE
EVERYONE CAN SEE US.

21:00.759 --> 21:03.261
{\an1}WELL, WE NEED TO FIND
SOMEPLACE QUICK BEFORE--

21:03.328 --> 21:04.596
Vicky: THERE YOU ARE!

21:04.663 --> 21:05.797
TOO LATE.

21:05.864 --> 21:07.432
HA!

21:09.034 --> 21:13.839
{\an5}WE STILL HAVE TIME
FOR ONE MORE RIDE
TOGETHER--

21:13.905 --> 21:15.774
THE MARRIAGE
GO ROUND.

21:15.841 --> 21:17.275
{\an1}I DO.

21:15.841 --> 21:17.275
I DO.

21:17.342 --> 21:18.243
I DO.

21:17.342 --> 21:18.243
I DO.

21:18.310 --> 21:20.979
WAIT! A RIDE? THAT'S IT!

21:21.046 --> 21:22.948
LET'S GO ON THAT ONE!

21:23.015 --> 21:24.282
[GASP]

21:25.851 --> 21:28.286
OH, GAH!

21:30.622 --> 21:34.726
{\an5}SORRY, KIDS,
BUT THIS KIDNEY
HAS GOT TO GO.

21:36.228 --> 21:38.196
{\an5}WE WON'T
TELL ANYBODY
ABOUT ADULT LAND,

21:38.263 --> 21:39.197
HONEST.

21:39.264 --> 21:41.233
WE KNOW YOU WON'T...

21:41.299 --> 21:42.567
[TEETH CHATTERING]

21:42.634 --> 21:44.670
{\an4}BECAUSE IF YOU DO,
YOU WON'T GET
TO KEEP THESE.

21:44.736 --> 21:48.573
{\an1}IT'S GAH, THE TALKING
SCANDINAVIAN SUPERDOLL.

21:48.640 --> 21:49.775
I HAVE A CALENDAR?

21:49.841 --> 21:51.143
Both: DEAL!

21:56.715 --> 21:58.917
I JUST LOVE
THE TUNNEL OF LOVE.

21:58.984 --> 22:01.319
IT'S SO NICE...
AND DARK!

22:01.386 --> 22:04.089
{\an1}YEP, THE PERFECT PLACE
TO MAKE A WISH.

22:04.156 --> 22:05.624
OR SMOOCH.

22:05.691 --> 22:07.426
RIGHT. WHAT?

22:08.860 --> 22:12.698
MMM-MMM. MMM.

22:12.764 --> 22:13.899
[GRUNT]

22:13.965 --> 22:14.966
AAH!

22:15.033 --> 22:17.002
[TIMMY SHOUTING]

22:18.403 --> 22:19.671
NICE DIAPERS.

22:19.738 --> 22:20.739
{\an1}THANKS.

22:25.711 --> 22:26.812
AAH!

22:26.878 --> 22:29.014
WHAT DID YOU DO
WITH GAH?

22:29.081 --> 22:32.451
{\an1}UH, HE HAD TO GO BACK
TO...NORWEGIA?

22:32.517 --> 22:34.886
NORWEGIA?

22:34.953 --> 22:36.788
I'M COMING, GAH!

22:36.855 --> 22:38.290
MUSH!

22:38.356 --> 22:41.093
TIME TO GO
MEET MY PARENTS.

22:42.427 --> 22:43.361
[SOB]

22:43.428 --> 22:45.330
I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE MISSED GAH.

22:45.397 --> 22:47.132
I BLAME YOU.

22:48.967 --> 22:50.936
Dolls: I'M NORWEGIRIFFIC.

22:51.002 --> 22:52.804
AHH.

22:51.002 --> 22:52.804
AHH.

22:52.871 --> 22:54.706
{\an1}TIMMY, I HOPE
YOU LEARNED A LESSON,

22:54.773 --> 22:56.341
THAT BEING TALL...

22:56.408 --> 22:58.176
{\an5}YEAH, YEAH,
DOESN'T MAKE ME
A BETTER PERSON.

22:58.243 --> 22:59.277
I KNOW.

22:59.344 --> 23:00.912
JUST DREAMIER.

23:00.979 --> 23:01.947
AAH!

23:02.013 --> 23:03.081
WHAT A DAY!

23:03.148 --> 23:04.816
{\an1}I GOT TO RIDE
THE HEART STOPPER,

23:04.883 --> 23:07.419
{\an1}EXPERIENCE PUBERTY,
AND GET RID OF VICKY.

23:07.486 --> 23:09.354
I WONDER WHERE SHE IS.

23:09.421 --> 23:11.423
Vicky: GAH, WHERE ARE YOU?

23:11.490 --> 23:13.925
I'VE LOST MY SUPERMODEL!

23:13.992 --> 23:16.161
AND THAT'S
THE PASSWORD.

23:16.228 --> 23:17.796
AAH!

23:24.402 --> 23:27.339
